{'book': {'publisher': 'Amistad Books for Young Readers', 'synopsis': 'In the groundbreaking tradition of his award-winning Monster and Bad Boy: A Memoir, Walter Dean Myers fashions a highly readable, powerful novel about the rules for success for young men, especially those navigating coming of age while Black.<br/>Share this book in the classroom, in a father-son reading group, or as a summer reading (or anytime) choice that\'s likely to spark conversation and be a favorite.<br/>"When the proprietor of a Harlem barbershop takes over as the court-appointed mentor for two troubled teenagers, he conveys the message that the future is built not only on hard work but on sustaining dreams as well." (Smithsonian magazine).<br/>In his introduction to Handbook for Boys, Walter Dean Myers wrote: "I know as a troubled teenager I would have loved to have a neighborhood barbershop to sit in and a group of worldly and knowledgeable men to counsel me. Thinking about this was my motivation in writing this book, hoping it will be, in the least, a jumping-off point for many interesting conversations about success."', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/93/08/9780064409308.jpg', 'title_long': 'Handbook for Boys: A Novel', 'edition': 'Illustrated', 'dimensions': 'Height: 6.75 Inches, Length: 4.19 Inches, Weight: 0.2425084882 Pounds, Width: 0.56 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 4.19}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.56}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.2425084882}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 6.75}}, 'pages': 211, 'date_published': '2003-04-01', 'subjects': ['Teen & Young Adult', 'Literature & Fiction', 'Boys & Men', 'Social & Family Issues', 'Coming of Age', 'Mysteries & Thrillers', 'Historical', 'Romantic', 'Law & Crime', 'Social Issues', 'Self Service', 'Custom Stores'], 'authors': ['Walter Dean Myers'], 'title': 'Handbook for Boys: A Novel', 'isbn13': '9780064409308', 'msrp': 8.99, 'binding':